   "source": [
    "# YOLOv8 Model Training for NID Card Detection\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook demonstrates how to train a YOLOv8 model to detect National ID (NID) cards in images. The trained model can then be used to crop the NID card from a larger image before performing OCR."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Install Dependencies"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "!pip install ultralytics"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Import Libraries"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import os\n",
    "from ultralytics import YOLO"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Prepare the Dataset Configuration File\n",
    "\n",
    "YOLOv8 requires a YAML file that specifies the paths to the training and validation datasets, the number of classes, and the names of the classes. We will create a `nid_card.yaml` file for our dataset."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Create the YAML file content\n",
    "yaml_content = f\"\\\"\n",
    "train: ../synthetic_nid_dataset/images/train/\n",
    "val: ../synthetic_nid_dataset/images/val/\n",
    "\n",
    "# number of classes\n",
    "nc: 1\n",
    "\n",
    "# class names\n",
    "names: ['nid_card']\n",
    `\"\"\"`\n",
    "\n",
    "# Write the content to the YAML file\n",
    "with open(\"nid_card.yaml\", \"w\") as f:\n",
    "    f.write(yaml_content)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. Train the Model\n",
    "\n",
    "Now we will train the YOLOv8 model on our dataset. We will use the `yolov8n.pt` pretrained model as a starting point."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Load a pretrained YOLOv8 model\n",
    "model = YOLO('yolov8n.pt')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Train the model\n",
    "results = model.train(\n",
    "    data='nid_card.yaml',\n",
    "    epochs=50,\n",
    "    imgsz=640,\n",
    "    batch=8,\n",
    "    name='yolo_nid_detection'\n",
    ")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 5. Evaluate the Model\n",
    "\n",
    "After training, we can evaluate the model on the validation set."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Evaluate the model\n",
    "results = model.val()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 6. Export the Model\n",
    "\n",
    "The trained model is saved in the `runs/detect/yolo_nid_detection/weights/best.pt` directory. This is the model that should be used in the backend application."
   ]
  }
